  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is pleased to hear that Fanny Garrison Villard and her children are coming to visit him at Rockledge. He tells of the birthdays and ages of Agnes Garrison, Charley (Garrison?), and Helen (Villard?). William Lloyd Garrison visited John Greenleaf Whittier in his new home in Danvers. William Lloyd Garrison will appear as a witness in the trial of William Craft, who is suing a man for libel for declaring that William Craft obtained money under false pretences. William Lloyd Garrison will attend Charles Callistus Burleigh&apos;s funeral.</subfield>
